The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 21 May is 42,114 (4,874.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 16 May, there were 75 new confirmed cases (8.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 09 May, there were 105 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 29% (30 fewer cases).
